content.description: Teenage Wasteland starts with a wicked mantle that gains an overhanging finger crack, and ends with big dinner plate holds to the top. The route is sustained and is a serious trad lead as the mantle is unprotected and the crack starts 15 ft above the deck.
content.protection: Cams from small to med range. There are no fixed anchors so bring your gear of all sizes for the top.
content.location: This route is located just left of the cave; easy access for toprope and walkoff.

content.description: "Look on the top of the rock across southeast from Teenage for two bolts, the anchors for Break In Tradition. The climb also shows as a light colored swath up the dark rock due to cleaning that has been done." - AAC
content.protection: "Look on the top of the rock across southeast from Teenage for two bolts, the anchors for Break In Tradition." - AAC
content.location: Southeast of Teenage Wasteland. Slabby wall right off the trail.

content.description: The home of two routes that are worth climbing. The routes are somewhat secluded as they are set off the main trail, but there is a cave near the climbs that is a popular destination spot for visiting hikers.
